1389":"1310–1389","1260–Male":"1260–Afdød","15 May 1341":"15. maj 1341","1341":"1341","1285":"1285","Abt 1308":"omkring 1308","1260":"1260","1291":"1291","1290":"1290","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1389":"1389","1453":"1453","1310":"1310","1320":"1320","about 1310":"omkring 1310","about 1320":"omkring 1320","about 1285":"omkring 1285","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","England":"England","Great Baddow, Essex, England":"Great Baddow, Essex, England","Baldock, Hertfordshire, England":"Baldock, Hertfordshire, England","Baddow, Chelmsford, Essex, England":"Chelmsford, Essex, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"about 1285–15 May 1341":"circa 1285–15 mei 1341","1285–1341":"1285–1341","1291–1320":"1291–1320","1310–1389":"1310–1389","1260–Male":"1260–Overleden","15 May 1341":"15 mei 1341","1341":"1341","1285":"1285","Abt 1308":"circa 1308","1260":"1260","1291":"1291","1290":"1290","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1389":"1389","1453":"1453","1310":"1310","1320":"1320","about 1310":"circa 1310","about 1320":"circa 1320","about 1285":"circa 1285","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","England":"England","Great Baddow, Essex, England":"Great Baddow, Essex, England","Baldock, Hertfordshire, England":"Baldock, Hertfordshire, England","Baddow, Chelmsford, Essex, England":"Chelmsford, Essex, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"about 1285–15 May 1341":"about 1285–15 May 1341","1285–1341":"1285–1341","1291–1320":"1291–1320","1310–1389":"1310–1389","1260–Male":"1260–Deceased","15 May 1341":"15 May 1341","1341":"1341","1285":"1285","Abt 1308":"about 1308","1260":"1260","1291":"1291","1290":"1290","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1389":"1389","1453":"1453","1310":"1310","1320":"1320","about 1310":"about 1310","about 1320":"about 1320","about 1285":"about 1285","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","England":"England","Great Baddow, Essex, England":"Great Baddow, Essex, England","Baldock, Hertfordshire, England":"Baldock, Hertfordshire, England","Baddow, Chelmsford, Essex, England":"Chelmsford, Essex, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Phelipp","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt, Hans, Heinz, Manfred, Dieter, Erhard, Erhardt, Guenther, Gunther, Helmut, Hilde, Inge.","German and Jewish (western Ashkenazic): from the personal name <i>Philipp</i> (see   Philip  ).","Scottish (Glamorgan) and English (southeastern): variant of   Philip  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Philip","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Varughese, Mathai, Babu, Reji, Anil, Binu, Neena, Prema, Raju, Reena, Susheela, Aleykutty.","Scottish, English, German, Dutch, and Jewish: from the Greek personal name <i>Philippos</i> (from <i>philein</i> ‘to love’ + <i>hippos</i> ‘horse’). In the New Testament this name is borne by one of the apostles; it was also borne by various other early Christian saints. It owes part of its popularity to the medieval romances about Alexander the Great, whose father was Philip of Macedon. As a Jewish name, it represents a borrowing of the personal name from Christians. As a Highland Scottish surname, it represents an Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Fhilib</b> ‘son of Philip’. In North America, the English form of the surname has absorbed cognates from other languages, e.g. Spanish   Felipe  , Catalan <b>Felip</b>, Polish, Czech, Slovak, Slovenian or Croatian   Filip  , Albanian   Filipi  , and their derivatives (see examples at   Philips  ). The name <i>Philip</i> is also found among Christians in southern India (compare   Philipose   and   Pothen  ), but since South Indians traditionally do not have hereditary surnames, the southern Indian name was in most cases registered as such only after immigration of its bearers to the US. Compare   Phillip  .","French (southern) and Breton (Finistère): variant of   Philippe  ."]},{"name":"Philippi","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Florian, Hans, Klaus, Kurt, Udo.","German, Dutch, Flemish, and French (mainly Alsace and Lorraine): Latinized (humanistic) patronymic from the personal name   Philipp   (German),   Philip   (Dutch), or   Philippe   (French), using the genitive of its Latin form <i>Philippus</i>. In southern France and Corsica this is a surname of Italian origin (compare 2 below).","Americanized form of Italian   Filippi  ."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":5,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":30,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":43,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":52,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Phelipp was born about 1285, in Baldock, Hertfordshire, England as the son of Wall Phelipp. He married Isabella de Chelmsford about 1308, in Chelmsford, Essex, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died on 15 May 1341, in England, at the age of 57."},"et":{"about 1285–15 May 1341":"umbes 1285–15. mai 1341","1285–1341":"1285–1341","1291–1320":"1291–1320","1310–1389":"1310–1389","1260–Male":"1260–Surnud","15 May 1341":"15. mai 1341","1341":"1341","1285":"1285","Abt 1308":"umbes 1308","1260":"1260","1291":"1291","1290":"1290","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1389":"1389","1453":"1453","1310":"1310","1320":"1320","about 1310":"umbes 1310","about 1320":"umbes 1320","about 1285":"umbes 1285","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","England":"England","Great Baddow, Essex, England":"Great Baddow, Essex, England","Baldock, Hertfordshire, England":"Baldock, Hertfordshire, England","Baddow, Chelmsford, Essex, England":"Chelmsford, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1285–15 May 1341":"noin 1285–15. toukokuuta 1341","1285–1341":"1285–1341","1291–1320":"1291–1320","1310–1389":"1310–1389","1260–Male":"1260–Kuollut","15 May 1341":"15. toukokuuta 1341","1341":"1341","1285":"1285","Abt 1308":"noin 1308","1260":"1260","1291":"1291","1290":"1290","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1389":"1389","1453":"1453","1310":"1310","1320":"1320","about 1310":"noin 1310","about 1320":"noin 1320","about 1285":"noin 1285","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","England":"England","Great Baddow, Essex, England":"Great Baddow, Essex, England","Baldock, Hertfordshire, England":"Baldock, Hertfordshire, England","Baddow, Chelmsford, Essex, England":"Chelmsford, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1285–15 May 1341":"environ 1285–15 mai 1341","1285–1341":"1285–1341","1291–1320":"1291–1320","1310–1389":"1310–1389","